<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued April 18 at 3:37PM EDT until April 18 at 7:00PM EDT by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM EDT THIS
EVENING...
* WHAT...Wet snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches.
* WHERE...Macomb and Oakland Counties.
* WHEN...From noon today to 7 PM EDT this evening.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will continue with snowfall rates
decreasing between 4 pm and 6 pm. Snow will then taper to
flurries later this evening into the overnight. The snowfall
rates will be high enough to allow for some wet snow and slush
accumulations onto the roads into the early evening.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
